               <history>
                  <origin>Possibly completed in <origPlace
                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7001502" key="place_7001502"
                        >Awadh</origPlace>; undated, but probably <date cert="medium"
                        calendar="#Gregorian" notBefore="1700" notAfter="1800">18th century
                        CE</date>.</origin>
                  <provenance><p>Previously owned by <persName role="fmo seal"
                           key="person_122375965" ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/122375965/"
                           >Jean-Baptiste Gentil (1726–1799 CE)</persName> as per his seal
                        impression on folio <locus from="1a" to="1a">1a</locus>. Presumably sold by
                        Gentil before his death or by his family thereafter; however the
                        circumstances of the volume's arrival in Britain remain
                     unclear.</p></provenance>
                  <provenance><p>Subsequently acquired by one <q>Mrs. Bainston</q>  (or <q>Barnston</q>?)
                        who presented it to the <orgName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/158082457"
                           >University of Manchester Library</orgName>.</p></provenance>
                  <acquisition>
